            <h4>Why vaccines are Important?</h4>
            <p class="card-text">Vaccines are not just important they are the very reason humanity has survived and thrived in the face of pandemics, plagues, and deadly diseases for centuries. In a world where misinformation spreads at the speed of a tweet, and fear-mongering has replaced scientific fact, refusing to vaccinate is not only a personal choice; it is a reckless act of negligence with profound consequences for public health. The denial of science the refusal to accept the overwhelming, irrefutable evidence that vaccines are safe and effective is not just dangerous; it’s criminal. If you still doubt the power of vaccines, it’s time to confront the harsh reality: your skepticism doesn’t just harm you it harms everyone. Vaccines don’t just protect the individual who gets vaccinated, they protect entire communities through a concept called herd immunity. So, let's be blunt: if you are still questioning the power of vaccines, you are choosing ignorance over science, selfishness over responsibility, and risk over safety. And the next time you think about questioning the safety of vaccines, ask yourself: who are you really putting at risk? Because the truth is, your refusal could be the very thing that sparks the next outbreak</p>
